{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":6688,"name":"april si","username":"april_si","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/a/a88e57/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-09T09:07:36.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello, I am artist and trying out Urho \u003ca href=\"http://Editor.sh\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eEditor.sh\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhenever I select the camera in Editor, a nice view pop in lower right corner and when detected it disappears.\u003cbr\u003e\nHow to do so that it always stays there?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnyway to pop out the camera view and resize it.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:51.218Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":27,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":136.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"april si","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://Editor.sh","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":266,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6694,"name":"","username":"setzer22","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-09T17:52:11.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWelcome to Urho3D!  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/smiley.png?v=5\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smiley:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm not able to reproduce that issue as I‚Äôm able to see the small camera view, even when manipulating the camera node (moving the camera) the viewport is still there and I‚Äôm able to see through the camera. Could you please clarify a bit more what are you doing when the problem occurs, and what exactly do you mean by ‚Äúwhen detected‚Äù?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:51.656Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":1.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":125,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6696,"name":"","username":"amit","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/a/ee7513/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-09T18:43:02.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI think when camera is deselected the said view disappears. It happens.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:51.808Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":1.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":170,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6697,"name":"april si","username":"april_si","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/a/a88e57/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-09T19:06:50.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks setzer22, \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOops, I meant when I \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-u\"\u003edeselected\u003c/span\u003e camera, not detected \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/blush.png?v=5\" title=\":blush:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":blush:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nWhenever I select some other node, the camera view disappears. Just want to keep it up while I set the scene.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:51.872Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":1.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"april si","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":266,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6700,"name":"","username":"setzer22","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-09T20:55:57.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm afraid that‚Äôs the intended behaviour of the Editor. Bear in mind that the editor is still far from production-ready, and you might not find all the desired features in it. Even though it‚Äôs a great tool for most use cases IMO.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat being said, It wouldn‚Äôt be difficult to come up with a quick hack in order to display a camera on the screen as a separate viewport without even touching the editor code, just by adding a component to the camera node. I‚Äôm also interested and I was working on something very similar just the other day, so I‚Äôm going to give it a try and post it here if I manage to do it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso, if you want, you can open a new thread in the Feature Request section, and ask for this feature to be included in the editor!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:52.067Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":1.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":125,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6706,"name":"Yao Wei Tjong","username":"weitjong","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/weitjong/{size}/4_2.png","created_at":"2015-07-10T01:35:58.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI agree with what setzer22 has said. But I want to add that currently the provided Editor is already capable to display multiple viewports. At the moment, the camera‚Äôs properties have to be manually adjusted. It should not be difficult to script that the viewport can be ‚Äòstick‚Äô to or associate to another camera component and therefore render from its point of view.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:52.507Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":6,"readers_count":5,"score":1.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"Yao Wei Tjong","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Admin","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":4,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6710,"name":"april si","username":"april_si","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/a/a88e57/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-10T08:15:48.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"setzer22\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ce7236/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e setzer22:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ejust by adding a component to the camera node\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat component is to be added to it and how.\u003cbr\u003e\nBut on the same thought train I was able to achieve some success. I just selected the camera and not the parent node, this displayed the viewport.\u003cbr\u003e\nThen I ‚Äúctrl‚Äù selected the node of the mesh to be moved/rotate/scale, now node transformation only applies to selected nodes not the selected camera  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/sunglasses.png?v=10\" title=\":sunglasses:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":sunglasses:\"\u003e .\u003cbr\u003e\n(Is that what you were saying setzer‚Ä¶)\u003cbr\u003e\n‚Ä¶ Thanks\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am able to do what i want but, would want some more non-hackish way.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI do not know much of coding, but can understand and do some changes  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/neutral_face.png?v=10\" title=\":neutral_face:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":neutral_face:\"\u003e  if I know where to do so. Ill try take some help.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Editor a great tool, and my work tool in urho sphere, few stuff like applying standard materials could be more intuitive and of course sticky camera, but still given urho‚Äôs team size it still well thought of, like pick light|geometries|‚Ä¶ and fill point|wire|geometries options.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:52.767Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":5,"readers_count":4,"score":1.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"april si","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":266,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6711,"name":"april si","username":"april_si","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/a/a88e57/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-10T08:45:02.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOk ‚Ä¶\u003cbr\u003e\nin file \u003ca href=\"http://EditorView.as\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eEditorView.as\u003c/a\u003e added slashes at line 663\u003cbr\u003e\n//if (renderer.numViewports \u0026gt; viewports.length)\u003cbr\u003e\n//    renderer.numViewports = viewports.length;\u003cbr\u003e\nit work for now\u003cbr\u003e\nHope this has no errors,\u003cbr\u003e\nAny more would require more work i suppose.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:52.841Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":5,"readers_count":4,"score":1.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"april si","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://EditorView.as","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":266,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6712,"name":"","username":"setzer22","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-10T09:25:50.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n april si:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[quote=‚Äúsetzer22‚Äù]just by adding a component to the camera node\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat component is to be added to it and how.[/quote]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe component I was talking about is not done. I was talking about doing it myself. It‚Äôs still a bit hackish but way more functional than Ctrl-Clicking that way. The workflow would basically be adding a component to the camera node which then would display said camera in a region of the screen (and you‚Äôd be able to define that region through the Component‚Äôs attributes). It‚Äôs really quick to do, and in fact I was working on a very similar thing just yesterday, but somehow the editor was preventing me to add more viewports to the renderer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[quote]\u003cbr\u003e\nOk ‚Ä¶\u003cbr\u003e\nin file \u003ca href=\"http://EditorView.as\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eEditorView.as\u003c/a\u003e added slashes at line 663\u003cbr\u003e\n//if (renderer.numViewports \u0026gt; viewports.length)\u003cbr\u003e\n// renderer.numViewports = viewports.length;\u003cbr\u003e\nit work for now\u003cbr\u003e\nHope this has no errors,\u003cbr\u003e\nAny more would require more work i suppose.[/quote]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd it seems you just have found the line responsible for that! I‚Äôm going to have a look now and see if I can code something quick, brb.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:52.907Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":4,"readers_count":3,"score":0.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://EditorView.as","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":125,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6713,"name":"","username":"setzer22","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-10T10:12:09.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eJust as I thought, the lines you commented out were responsible for hiding the camera once un-selected. By removing those, the viewport is never removed and you‚Äôll always see the last camera you clicked.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat‚Äôs a workaround and it works, but it‚Äôs not a proper fix, because each time you select the camera (or a different one), a new viewport is created on top of the other one, so you‚Äôll end up with lots of viewports and that would eventually slow up the editor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWithout removing those lines, the problem is the editor removes all the viewports the user might have created so my component won‚Äôt work until this is fixed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor now having those lines removed allows for the functionality you needed so until there‚Äôs a fix it should be ok to do that. It would take a while until you notice a substantial slowdown anyway, but bear in mind that performance might degrade.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnyway, I‚Äôve made a small script that draws a viewport with the camera it‚Äôs attached to anywhere on the screen. That would allow for more functionality like dislpaying the contents of multiple cameras if needed, and allow the user to customize the size of the viewport as well. Once I find a fix for this I‚Äôll post it on the Code Exchange section of the forum! For now I guess the workaround is good enough?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:52.990Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":5,"readers_count":4,"score":1.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":125,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6715,"name":"april si","username":"april_si","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/a/a88e57/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-10T12:21:06.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks for all the help ‚Ä¶\u003cbr\u003e\nI would not be able do anything more even if I want to.\u003cbr\u003e\nThis was lucky too ‚Ä¶ I saw \u003ca href=\"http://EditorView.as\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eEditorView.as\u003c/a\u003e in \u003ca href=\"http://editor.as\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eeditor.as\u003c/a\u003e, looked in to file, luckily found the function and removed the ones which were hiding the viewport.\u003cbr\u003e\nI was thinking to change ‚ÄúselectedComponents‚Äù with allComponents, but did not know where allcomponents are ‚Ä¶ I even don‚Äôt know what language it is  \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/smiley.png?v=5\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smiley:\"\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nI think I should focus on art.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShould i request this feature from Urho team?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks again for helping me out, this really helped my workflow.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:53.146Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":4,"readers_count":3,"score":0.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"april si","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://EditorView.as","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0},{"url":"http://editor.as","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":266,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":6716,"name":"","username":"setzer22","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-07-10T13:28:32.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe problem with changing selectedComponents with all the components in the scene would be that if more than a camera is present in the scene, only the first would ever get drawn.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe editor is written in AngelScript, it‚Äôs a scripting language with a C+¬±like syntax that‚Äôs used in Urho.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can make a feature request for this. Having a way to keep the last selected camera shouldn‚Äôt be difficult to fix. Maybe a better (but also more difficult) way of implementing the feature could be something like:\u003cbr\u003e\nright click on camera -\u0026gt; View in window -\u0026gt; A UI window pops up with the camera view and you can move it and resize it.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:05:53.212Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":4,"readers_count":3,"score":0.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1170,"topic_slug":"sticky-camera-view-in-editor","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":n